CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 3, 1955, pg. 4 reads: "Before Owl's Greenlight - Before appearing before Common Pleas Court Judge Clarence B. Nixon, opposing sides in Owl Cab Company battle, agreed in the courtroom corridor that the petition by Silas Knox, to place the company into the hands of a receivorship, should be dismissed. Judge Nixon signed the consent order which gave Owl's new management a legal greenlight for its plans for efficient city service....The right photo shows, left to right, Silas Knox, and his attorneys, Alexander Cooper, and Bernard Goodman. -Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Silas Knox, Atty. Alexander Cooper, and Atty. Bernard Goodman in corridor of Allegheny County Courthouse
